<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,655,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="334">
The new taxon shares following synapomorphies with the members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[991,1109,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Aphodiini">Aphodiini</taxonomicName>
: 1) labrum and mandibles invisible in antero-dorsal view; 2) scutellum well visible in dorsal view; 3) pronotum without any longitudinal groove; head without any longitudinal groove or costa; 4) protibia not perpendicularly truncate apically; 5) metatibial spurs separated by basal tarsomere; abdominal ventrites not fused, freely moveable.
</paragraph>
